parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or shift into alternate gears while in motion, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the transmission warning light illuminates
the vehicle shifts into alternate gears while in motion
the vehicle hesitates or jerks while shifting
and the dynamic drive system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration of the vehicle can cause accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates on its own
the vehicle shifts into reverse or neutral while in motion
and the vehicle crashes into objects or other vehicles.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the vehicle to stall, lose power, or experience other issues that can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls while driving
the warning lights on the instrument panel illuminate
and the vehicle experiences electrical issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of sensors can cause the vehicle to experience issues with the transmission, engine, or other systems, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission warning light illuminates
the vehicle shifts into alternate gears while in motion
and the dynamic drive system fails.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the airbag system can lead to the non-deployment of airbags in the event of a crash, increasing the risk of injury or fatality to occupants.
symptoms: Illumination of the airbag warning light
faulty passenger occupancy sensor
faulty driver seat mat sensor
faulty passenger seat mat sensor
faulty steering angle sensor
airbag warning light remains illuminated
passenger restraint system fault light illuminates
driver restraint system fault light illuminates
airbag may not operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake vacuum pump can cause the brake pedal to become soft or spongy, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal extends to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
a chirping sound is heard during idle
oil leaks into the brake booster
and the brake pedal requires excessive pressure to stop the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake booster can cause the brake pedal to become hard or difficult to press, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal is hard or difficult to press
the brake pedal requires excessive pressure to stop the vehicle
and the vehicle takes longer to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hydraulic system can cause the brake pedal to become soft or spongy, leading to increased stopping distances and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal extends to the floorboard
the vehicle takes longer to stop
and oil leaks into the brake booster.
